ps)","fresh mint leaves, for garnishing","lemon wedges, to serve"]}],"id":"r134229","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-l4J5RciHx78\/XZMvzjP4FfI\/AAAAAAAAaWY\/EgilI8wHTCALPT8-ma9Hc-qd7I0qYS-bgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_pz49qNM3llG5AdTr.png","title":"Tandoori chicken","publishedAt":"2017-07-03T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"26.9 g","fat":"23.4 g","uom":"per 1 portions","carbohydrates":"10.1 g","calories":"1515 kJ \/ 360 kcal"},"usefulItems":"sealable sterilised jar, large bowl, 6 wooden skewers, metal skewers, baking tray (30 x 40 cm), aluminium foil, plastic wrap, bowl, refrigerator, oven grill","hintsAndTricks":["To make you own garlic paste, ginger paste and ghee, please refer to the recipe on this recipe chip.","You can store Tandoori paste in the refrigerator for up to 4 weeks or place into ice cube trays and store in the freezer for up to 3 months.","The tandoori marinade (yoghurt and tandoori paste) also works well with fish and lamb.","We served our Tandoori chicken with Mint and peanut chutney. Please refer to the recipe on this recipe chip."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","45m","6 portions"]}